        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>üá¶üáπ Austria: Political change and far-right </strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"> 
            Austria is experiencing political uncertainty following Chancellor Karl Nehammer's resignation after <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h1-1-failed-coalition-talks" target="_blank">failed coalition talks</a> between his party and the Social Democrats. Nehammer's resignation raises concerns about potential cooperation between the Austrian People's Party and the far-right Freedom Party, which received 29% votes in the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h1-2-recent-elections" target="_blank">recent elections</a>. This collaboration could further polarize Austrian politics, as the Freedom Party, led by Herbert Kickl, now <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h1-3-holds-the-strongest-position" target="_blank">holds the strongest position</a> in parliament since World War II. Alexander Schallenberg from the Austrian People‚Äôs Party has taken over as the interim chancellor.
          </p>
          </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>üá∫üá¶ Ukraine: Counterattack and retaliation</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
            Ukraine has launched <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h2-4-a-surprise-counterattack" target="_blank">a surprise counterattack</a> in Russia‚Äôs Kursk region, where it has maintained a presence since August. Ukrainian forces are encountering resistance from Russian and North Korean troops. To mitigate war fatigue, President Zelensky appeared on <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h2-5-lex-fridman-podcast" target="_blank">Lex Fridman's podcast</a> to counter pro-Russian narratives and address concerns about U.S. aid. Ukraine‚Äôs 47th Brigade released a video of a massive Russian attack repelled in the Kursk Oblast, where 4000 North Korean troops were killed.
          </p>
          </mj-text>

          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>üá®üá¶ Canada: Trudeau‚Äôs resignation and next PM</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"> 
            Canadian Prime Minister <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h3-6-justin-trudeau-has-resigned" target="_blank">Justin Trudeau has resigned</a> as leader of the Liberal Party after nine years amid declining public support and internal dissent. Trudeau's tenure saw progressive policies like legalizing cannabis and establishing affordable child care. However, he faced criticism over inflation and economic challenges, particularly following a political crisis related to Trump‚Äôs tariffs at the end of 2024. High-profile contenders Mark Carney and Anita Anand are expected to run for leadership, but upcoming elections <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h3-7-favor-the-conservatives" target="_blank">favor the Conservatives</a>, led by Pierre Poilievre. Canada‚Äôs Liberal Party will announce the country's next prime minister on March 9 after a leadership vote following Justin Trudeau's resignation this week.
          </p>
