          <strong>üáÆüá© Indonesia: BRICS membership and China wishes</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"> 
            Indonesia has officially <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h4-8-joined-the-BRICS" target="_blank">joined the BRICS</a>, becoming its tenth full member. Jakarta views membership as a step towards global collaboration and sustainable development. Brazil, the 2025 BRICS president, welcomed Indonesia, noting shared goals like reforming global governance and promoting South-South cooperation. Indonesia, the fourth most populous country, has the largest economy in Southeast Asia. The BRICS accounted for 46% of the world's population and 35% of global gross domestic product before Indonesia‚Äôs inclusion. China has extended its <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h4-9-congatulations-to-indonesia" target="_blank">congratulations to Indonesia</a> and added, "We believe that Indonesia will make active contributions to the development of BRICS.‚Äù
          </p>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>üá∫üá≤ USA: Trump‚Äôs bold claims and backlash</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
            Donald Trump's recent comments that China controls the Panama Canal <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h5-10-were-termed-nonsense" target="_blank">were termed "nonsense"</a> by Panamanian Foreign Minister Javier Martinez-Acha, who asserted that Panama operates the canal independently. Justin Trudeau rejected Trump's idea of a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h5-11-canada-us-merger" target="_blank">Canada-US merger</a>, stating, "There isn't a snowball's chance in hell." French Foreign Minister Jean-Noel Barrot cautioned Trump against threatening <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h5-12-eu-sovereignty" target="_blank">EU sovereignty</a>, emphasizing that the EU would defend its borders. Claudia Sheinbaum took <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-h5-13-a-sarcastic-jab" target="_blank">a sarcastic jab</a> at Trump over his idea of renaming the Gulf of Mexico to the Gulf of America.
