          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">On this day in 1861, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-01-2025-bq6-19-alabama-seceded" target="_blank">Alabama seceded</a> from the Union, becoming the fourth state leading up to the American Civil War. Montgomery, Alabama, would eventually serve as the capital of the Confederacy. The Civil War began three months later, on April 12, 1861. The South seceded from the Union primarily for two reasons: to maintain slavery and due to dissatisfaction over states' rights. Debates continue regarding which of these factors was the more significant cause.</p>
